{"article_id":"JBo7f9mK7Parsfht","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The United States surpassed 3 million coronavirus infections on Wednesday , a grim milestone","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"as the virus surges in more than half of all states ,","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"and a predicted waning of infections this summer never occurred .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Data from the John Hopkins University Coronavirus Resource Center showed","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"the U.S. had 3,009,611 cases at midday on Wednesday .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"On Tuesday , the U.S. set a record with 60,000 new cases .","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"California and Texas both had more than 10,000 new cases in a single day ,","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"shattering previous records .","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Arizona , Florida , and South Carolina led the world in new cases over the last seven days ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"according to New York Times data .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"Hospitals in Florida have run out of beds in their intensive care units ,","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"even as Gov . Ron DeSantis","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"Ronald Dion DeSantisFlorida records more than 15,000 new COVID-19 cases in one day , the highest single-day increase in any state","depth":6},{"id":13,"text":"Teachers union president casts doubt on schools","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"reopening full-time","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"DeSantis on Florida schools reopening :","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"'If you can do Walmart , '","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"then 'we absolutely can do the schools '","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"MORE ( R )","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"continues to downplay the situation","depth":7},{"id":20,"text":"and refuses to release critical information about hospitalizations .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"While experts previously predicted a summer lull in infections ,","depth":4},{"id":22,"text":"that never materialized .","depth":4},{"id":23,"text":"Many states ,","depth":6},{"id":24,"text":"facing pressure from business leaders and from the White House ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"rushed to reopen","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"without fully anticipating the impact on new infections .","depth":5},{"id":27,"text":"White House coronavirus task force coordinator Deborah Birx on Tuesday said in a Sirius XM interview","depth":5},{"id":28,"text":"that states ignored guidelines","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"put in place by federal and local public health officials ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"and \" stepped on the gas \"","depth":8},{"id":31,"text":"while reopening ,","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"causing this new surge .","depth":7},{"id":33,"text":"After calling on governors to reopen state economies ,","depth":4},{"id":34,"text":"the Trump administration has now shifted its attention to pressure schools to fully reopen in the fall .","depth":4},{"id":35,"text":"The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention recently released guidance","depth":6},{"id":36,"text":"for safely reopening schools ,","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"but President Trump","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Donald John TrumpDavis :","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"Supreme Court decision is bad news for Trump ,","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"good news for Vance Meadows","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"trying to root out suspected White House leakers","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"by feeding them info :","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"Axios Pressley hits DeVos over reopening schools :","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"' I would n't trust you to care for a house plant","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"let alone my child '","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"MORE on Wednesday tweeted his displeasure with his own public health agency .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"He said","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"the guidelines were too burdensome and `` expensive , ''","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"and indicated","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"he would be meeting with the agency in an effort","depth":12},{"id":51,"text":"to change them .","depth":12},{"id":52,"text":"Testing capacity is being strained in those states with the largest number of new infections ,","depth":5},{"id":53,"text":"and supply chain issues","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"that plagued the country early in the pandemic","depth":7},{"id":55,"text":"have resurfaced .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"While Trump and other administration officials have latched onto a declining fatality rate as a sign of progress ,","depth":3},{"id":57,"text":"Anthony Fauci","depth":4},{"id":58,"text":"Anthony FauciSunday shows -","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"Spotlight shifts to reopening schools","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"US testing official :","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"'Dr . Fauci is not 100 percent right '","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"Trump flails","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"as audience dwindles","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"and ratings plummet","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"MORE on Tuesday said","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"focusing on that one statistic is a `` false narrative . ''","depth":11},{"id":67,"text":"`` There 's so many other things","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"that are very dangerous and bad about this virus ,","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"do n't get yourself into a false complacency , \"","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"Fauci , the nation 's leading infectious disease expert , said .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"Deaths are a lagging indicator in an outbreak ,","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"and will rise","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"as people generally don ' t die until weeks after they become sick .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"In addition , many of the newly infected have been young people ,","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"who generally tend to be healthier","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"\" But that doesn ' t mean","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"that you could not get seriously ill , \"","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"Fauci said .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":157,"left":111,"right":156,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":111,"